(254, 1, '2016-06-13 10:51:10', '2016-06-13 03:51:10', '<img src="http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/muaythai-1.jpg" width="315" height="470" srcset="http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/muaythai-1.jpg 315w, http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/muaythai-1-201x300.jpg 201w, http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/muaythai-1-230x343.jpg 230w" title="Muay Thai" alt="muaythai" class="so-widget-image">\r\n<h3 style="color: red;">MUAY THAI</h3>\r\n<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">Muay Thai is a form of traditional martial art that originated in Thailand but has now gained worldwide popularity. It is a national sport in Thailand. It is known for its deadly counter striking arsenal. And Muay Thai became a skill based sport. Muay Thai is a martial art that is unlike any other, rich in the proud heritage of an entire nation. It is very much a patient art â you wait for the right opening then strike. It is an intense cardio workout it burns calories, improves strength, muscle tone, muscle endurance and flexibility. Muay Thai is a great workout option for those who are interested in practical, traditional martial arts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="color: #ffffff;">Every Muay Thai classes are designed for progression learning in each student. Muay Thai students may progress to their level by way of attending many classes each week and understanding the curriculum module. Each student will passes their prajeat Muay Thai for class progression and certification.</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<a href="http://www.google.com"><span class="roll-button"> VIEW SCHEDULE </span></a>\r\n<p><a name="fitthai"></a></p>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/fitthai.jpg" width="315" height="470" srcset="http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/fitthai.jpg 315w, http://localhost/muaysukhothai/wp-content/uploads/2016/06/fitthai-201x300.jpg 201w, http://localhost/muaysukhothai